<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Zyrxil:
[I]Ok, not exactly between -worlds-, per se, but walking the darkness nonetheless using a common/simple exploit. I'm feeling lazy so I'll skimp on screenshots  :p

Anyway, I was wasting some time by teleport exploring the Dark Forest map, scan throwing the pyramaids into mag fog areas where you shouldn't be able to go, starting from the Imp Castle plateau (cause well, you can't throw Up onto some high ledge you can't see). Well, I did this for a bit, then managed to teleport into a position right between a tree and a rock, where my line of sight -everywhere- was blocked, thus preventing me from throwing a pyramaid. Just on a whim, I throw a pyramaid and just scrolled with it really a long way south/down. Suddenly, I noticed the red cross on the cursor was gone for some reason, so I threw it ..somewhere. I tried to teleport, but it told me the stones weren't working. Not knowing that they didn't work while one of the pyramaids was still "traveling", I just kept trying anyway. Lo and behold, woosh, in a swirl I teleported into Nothingness.

Or rather, I ended up a bit north outside the outer boundaries of King Dunatrim's throne room. And of course being Divine I could exist there in nothingness, and explore oh...all 20 dungeon maps at once, including one that was probably the treasure dungeon I never visited, and what seemed to be an unused section of the Dwarven Halls that was cut, including treasure chests (yes, some with items, for some reason), glows without those blue light pillars under them, and of course, casks of beer  ;) . Being nowhere, it was possible to achieve a compulsive mapper/explorer's dream- clearing those damn annoying half squares of fog sometimes left on the outer walls of a dungeon that you simply can't clear from inside, however close you are standing to the wall  :) .

I guess the game simply is fooled, by the mere fact that you aren't on the same map as you are throwing to, that you have direct line of sight there. And BTW, this works on -all- the aboveland maps, from anywhere. On the Rivertowen underground map, there's also this little room, sorta like a study, with a desk and a metal fenced area, with stairs that lead up to...the church, seemingly from the confessional booth. Weird. There also exists a small walled off room with lots of keys, and some items you receive for various quests. You can even walk back -up-, toward the aboveground map, and run around the borders (though still not on the areas that have terrain but aren't accessible normally. those simply don't allow you to move while on them).

And to get back to normal space? Quite elementary, my dear Watson, simply use a set of stairs, a door, a ladder- from the other side.

Anyway, have fun, and if this has been done before I'll feel really foolish for typing so much  :p[/I][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
